Many learners have been forced out of school by teenage pregnancies, early marriages and child labour.More worrying is that some teenagers were involved in crime, drug abuse, sex orgies and wild parties. At last, schools have reopened. Sadly, thousands of learners have failed to show up in class. This has arisen fear of massive dropouts caused by the prolonged closure of learning institutions. 
Many of these learners have been forced out of school by teenage pregnancies, early marriages and child labour.



